<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the area of a kite</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A kite has diagonals of lengths <strong>{@d1@} cm</strong> and <strong>{@d2@} cm</strong>.
</p>

<p>
The diagonals of a kite bisect each other at right angles.
</p>

[[jsxgraph]]
var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {
    boundingbox: [-10, 10, 10, -10],
    axis: false,
    showCopyright: false
});

// STACK values
var d1 = {#d1#};
var d2 = {#d2#};

var h1 = d1/2;
var h2 = d2/2;

// Points
var A = board.create('point', [0, h2], {name: 'A'});
var B = board.create('point', [-h1, 0], {name: 'B'});
var C = board.create('point', [h1, 0], {name: 'C'});
var D = board.create('point', [0, -h2], {name: 'D'});

// Kite
board.create('polygon', [A, B, D, C], {
    fillColor: '#e6f2ff',
    borders: {strokeColor: 'black', strokeWidth: 2}
});

// Diagonals
board.create('segment', [A, D], {dash: 2});
board.create('segment', [B, C], {dash: 2});

// Labels
board.create('text', [h1/2, 0.5, d1 + " cm"]);
board.create('text', [0.5, h2/2, d2 + " cm"]);
[[/jsxgraph]]
<ol>
<li>
<p>Calculate the area of the kite.</p>
<p>Area = [[input:ans1]] cm² [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the diagonals to calculate the length of a side.</p>

<p>
Length = [[input:ans2]] cm [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]
</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Find the size of the angles of the kite (in degrees).</p>
<p>
Angle 1 = [[input:ans3]]° [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]<br>
Angle 2 = [[input:ans4]]° [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]
</p>
<p><i>(Give your answer to 1 decimal places where possible)</i></p>
</li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p><strong>(a) Area of the kite</strong></p>
<p>
The area of a kite is given by:
\[
\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times d_1 \times d_2
\]
</p>

<p>
Substituting the values:
\[
\text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times {@d1@} \times {@d2@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\text{Area} = {@ta1@} \text{ cm}^2
\]
</p>

<p><strong>(b) Length of the kite</strong></p>

<p>
The diagonals of a kite bisect each other at right angles, forming right-angled triangles.
</p>

<p>
Half of each diagonal is:
\[
\frac{d_1}{2} = {@h1@}, \quad \frac{d_2}{2} = {@h2@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Using Pythagoras’ theorem to find the side length:
\[
\text{side}^2 = {@h1@}^2 + {@h2@}^2
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\text{side} = \sqrt{{@h1@}^2 + {@h2@}^2} = {@ta2@}
\]
</p>
<p><strong>(c) Angles of the kite</strong></p>

<p>
The diagonals form right triangles, allowing us to use trigonometry.
</p>

<p>
Consider one of the triangles:
\[
\tan\left(\frac{\theta}{2}\right) = \frac{{@h2@}}{{@h1@}}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\frac{\theta}{2} = \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{{@h2@}}{{@h1@}}\right)
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\theta = 2 \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{{@h2@}}{{@h1@}}\right)
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
\theta = {@ta3@}^\circ
\]
</p>
<p>
The other angle in the kite is:
\[
180^\circ - {@ta3@} = {@ta4@}^\circ
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
